{
 "response": "# Perspective Audit \u2014 Dense Admin Settings Panel With Jargon\n\n**Invocation source:** Escalation list from a11y-critic (no incoming `A11y Evidence Finding` block; traceability fields synthesized below for new CRITICAL/MAJOR findings).\n\n**Escalated perspectives (deep-reviewed):**\n- Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 HIGH\n- Magnification & Reflow \u2014 HIGH\n- Screen Reader & Semantic Structure \u2014 MEDIUM\n- Environmental Contrast \u2014 MEDIUM\n\n**Not escalated (LOW \u2014 not reviewed, per protocol Step 1):** Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Auditory Access, Keyboard & Motor Access.\n\n> Scope note: The native checkbox target is `36\u00d720 px` (`.toggle-switch input`, height `20px` < `24px`). That is a 2.5.8 Target Size (Minimum) concern living in **Keyboard & Motor Access**, which the critic rated LOW. The protocol forbids running LOW checklists, so it is flagged here as an out-of-scope observation only \u2014 not audited or scored. If the critic's LOW rating on that perspective is wrong, re-escalate; this audit does not.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 1 \u2014 Magnification & Reflow (HIGH)\n\n**JTBD checklist:**\n\n| Item (WCAG) | Result | Note |\n|---|---|---|\n| Reflows to single column at 320px, no horizontal scroll (1.4.10) | **FINDING** | Fixed 3-column grid, no reflow mechanism. See M1. |\n| Focused elements never obscured by sticky/fixed chrome (2.4.11) | N/A | No sticky/fixed elements in component. |\n| Text scales to 200% without overflow/truncation (1.4.4) | **FINDING** | 9px base on section headers; see M2. |\n| Adapts to text-spacing overrides (1.4.12) | **FINDING (verify)** | No fixed heights, but narrow columns at risk; see M3. |\n| Hover/focus content dismissible, hoverable, persistent (1.4.13) | N/A | No tooltips/popovers exist (their *absence* is a Cognitive finding, not a 1.4.13 issue). |\n\n**Red flag check:** \"Two-axis scrolling at 320px equivalent viewport\" \u2014 **FIRES** (auto-CRITICAL). Grid items default to `min-width: auto`, so the three columns cannot shrink below the min-content width of their longest labels (e.g., \"Enable HSTS preloading\", \"stale-while-revalidate cache\"). Summed min-content (~3\u00d7110px) plus gaps and padding exceeds 320px, forcing horizontal scroll. \"Text hidden/overlapping at 200%\" and \"tooltip disappears\" red flags do not fire.\n\n**Finding:** Layout does not reflow \u2014 a fixed three-column CSS grid with no media query, `minmax()`, or `auto-fit` means the panel keeps three columns at every width, producing two-axis scrolling at 320px CSS px / 400% zoom.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.10 Reflow\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** CRITICAL (red flag: two-axis scroll at 320px)\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** CSS `.settings-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; }` with fixture comment \"no reflow below 320px CSS pixels\"; no `@media` query anywhere in the stylesheet; JSX renders three fixed `.settings-column` siblings.\n**Fix:** Replace fixed tracks with `grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 16rem), 1fr));` (or a `@media (max-width: 40rem)` single-column fallback) so columns stack before content overflows. `[Visual confirmation recommended \u2014 capture a 400% zoom / 320px screenshot to verify no residual horizontal scrollbar.]`\n\n**Finding:** Section headers render at 9px, an illegibility barrier that is worst for the low-vision users this perspective protects and that inverts the visual hierarchy (headers smaller than the 13px labels beneath them). WCAG sets no absolute minimum font size, so the primary hook is that heavy zoom is required to read them \u2014 which in turn triggers the 1.4.10 reflow failure above, compounding the barrier.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.4 Resize Text (compounds 1.4.10; cognitive-hierarchy impact tracked under Perspective 7)\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** CSS `.settings-column h2 { font-size: 9px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }`; fixture comment \"9px font size \u2014 below readable threshold\". Labels below are `.toggle-label { font-size: 13px }` \u2014 larger than their own headings.\n**Fix:** Raise section headers to \u226514px (ideally 16px) and ensure they are visually larger/heavier than the item labels they group. Keep uppercase only if letter-spacing and size preserve legibility.\n\n**Finding:** Text-spacing overrides may overflow the already-cramped columns. No fixed text-container heights exist (good for vertical spacing), but added letter/word spacing on long technical labels inside narrow grid columns risks clipping/overlap.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.12 Text Spacing\n**Perspective:** Magnification & Reflow\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `.toggle-label` and `.settings-column h2` set no `height`/`overflow`; risk is confined to horizontal fit within `1fr` columns. `[Human verification required \u2014 apply the WCAG 1.4.12 text-spacing bookmarklet and confirm no clipping/overlap.]`\n**Fix:** Verify after the reflow fix (M1); single-column stacking largely resolves horizontal text-spacing pressure.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 2 \u2014 Environmental Contrast (MEDIUM)\n\n**JTBD checklist:**\n\n| Item (WCAG) | Result | Note |\n|---|---|---|\n| Normal text \u2265 4.5:1 (1.4.3) | **FINDING** | `#e53e3e` red at 4.13:1; see C1. |\n| Large text \u2265 3:1 (1.4.3) | N/A | No large text below threshold. |\n| UI component/state boundaries \u2265 3:1 (1.4.11) | PASS | Button `#2b6cb0` outline = 5.42:1 vs white; native checkboxes retain UA styling. |\n| Color never the sole indicator (1.4.1) | PASS | Error carries text (\"ERR_CSP_001\"); required carries the `*` glyph \u2014 both are non-color cues, so 1.4.1 is not violated (the *weakness* of those cues is captured under other perspectives). |\n| Instructions not by sensory characteristic alone (1.3.3) | PASS | No \"click the red one on the right\"\u2013style instructions. |\n| Functional in forced-colors mode | PASS (source-level) | Native `<button>`/`<input>` and text glyphs survive forced-colors; no CSS `outline: none` or background-only affordances. |\n\n**Red flag check:** None fire. Body text is `#111` (very high contrast); the error is not color-*only* (has text); interactive elements remain distinguishable in forced-colors. Note the red is **4.13:1**, above the 3:1 body-text auto-CRITICAL floor \u2014 so this is MAJOR, not CRITICAL.\n\n**Finding:** The single red token `#e53e3e` on white measures **4.13:1**, below the 4.5:1 minimum for normal text. It is used for both inline error text (11px) and the required asterisk (9px) \u2014 two normal-text uses, both failing.\n**WCAG:** 1.4.3 Contrast (Minimum)\n**Perspective:** Environmental Contrast\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `.error-inline { color: #e53e3e; font-size: 11px }` and `.required-asterisk { color: #e53e3e; font-size: 9px }`. Measured contrast of `#e53e3e` on `#fff` = 4.13:1 (fails 4.5:1).\n**Fix:** Darken the error/required red to \u22654.5:1 on white (e.g., `#c53030` \u2248 5.9:1, or `#b91c1c` \u2248 6.8:1). Apply to both `.error-inline` and `.required-asterisk`.\n\n**Checks that PASSED (stated to show the audit is not flagging everything):** section-header `#666` on white = **5.74:1** (its defect is *size*, not contrast); button text `#fff` on `#2b6cb0` = **5.42:1**; body labels `#111` and intro `#555` (7.46:1) both pass.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 6 \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (MEDIUM)\n\n**JTBD checklist:**\n\n| Item (WCAG) | Result | Note |\n|---|---|---|\n| Landmark regions present/correct (1.3.1) | PASS | `<main className=\"admin-settings\">` present. |\n| Heading hierarchy logical, h1 present (2.4.6) | PASS | `<h1>Server Configuration</h1>` \u2192 three `<h2>`. Semantically correct even though visually 9px. |\n| Informative images have alt; decorative `alt=\"\"` (1.1.1) | N/A | No images. |\n| DOM order matches visual order (1.3.2) | PASS | No `order`/reordering; columns render Security\u2192Performance\u2192Logging in source order. |\n| Unique descriptive `<title>` (2.4.2) | N/A (verify) | Component scope \u2014 no document `<title>`; app-level check. |\n| Link text describes destination (2.4.4) | N/A | No links. |\n| `lang` on `<html>` (3.1.1) | N/A (verify) | App-level; not in component source. |\n| Foreign-language phrases wrapped (3.1.2) | N/A | None. |\n| Every input has associated visible label (3.3.2) | PASS | `<label htmlFor={t.id}>` \u2194 `<input id={t.id}>`; accessible name resolves to the label text. |\n| Errors identify field + `aria-describedby` (3.3.1) | **FINDING** | Error not associated; see S1. |\n| Custom widgets use correct ARIA roles (4.1.2) | **FINDING** | Required *state* not exposed; see S2. |\n| Status messages use `aria-live` appropriately (4.1.3) | **FINDING** | No live region for save/unsaved state; unreliable alert-on-mount; see S1/S3. |\n| SPA route changes managed | N/A | Single component, no routing. |\n\n**Red flag check:** None fire \u2014 `<main>` is present, every input has a label, widgets are native (correct implicit roles), and `lang` is out of component scope. No auto-CRITICAL.\n\n**Finding:** The validation error is not programmatically tied to its field. The error `<span role=\"alert\">ERR_CSP_001</span>` sits as a sibling of the checkbox with no `aria-describedby` on the input and no `aria-invalid`. A screen-reader user who Tabs to the CSP checkbox hears only \"Enforce Content Security Policy, checkbox, not checked\" \u2014 the error is never conveyed in context. Additionally, the error text is present in the initial data, so `role=\"alert\"` firing on mount is unreliable (assertive live regions announce on insertion/change, not dependably at first render).\n**WCAG:** 3.3.1 Error Identification (with 4.1.3 Status Messages)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author)\n**Evidence:** JSX in `renderToggleGroup`: `<input type=\"checkbox\" id={t.id} ... />` has no `aria-describedby`/`aria-invalid`; the sibling `<span role=\"alert\">{t.error}</span>` is unreferenced; `SECURITY_TOGGLES` seeds `csp` with `error: 'ERR_CSP_001'` at mount.\n**Fix:** Give each error a stable id, set `aria-describedby={errorId}` and `aria-invalid=\"true\"` on the input, and reserve `role=\"alert\"` for errors surfaced *after* a user action (validation on Save), not for errors baked into initial state.\n\n**Finding:** Required state is invisible to assistive tech. The required inputs (`hsts`, `cors`, `access-log`) carry no `required` or `aria-required=\"true\"` attribute, and the only visible cue \u2014 the asterisk \u2014 is `aria-hidden=\"true\"`. The a11y tree therefore exposes no \"required\" property at all; a screen-reader user cannot tell which toggles are mandatory.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (missing required *state*)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author)\n**Evidence:** `SECURITY_TOGGLES`/`LOGGING_TOGGLES` mark `required: true`, but the JSX renders only `<span className=\"required-asterisk\" aria-hidden=\"true\">*</span>` and never emits `required`/`aria-required` on `<input>`.\n**Fix:** Add `aria-required=\"true\"` (or native `required`) to required inputs; expose the requirement in the accessible name/description as well (see Perspective 7, D5b).\n\n**Finding:** Save/unsaved status is never announced. `handleToggle` sets `saved=false` and `handleSave` sets `saved=true`, but no `aria-live` region reflects either transition. A screen-reader user gets no confirmation that Save succeeded and no notice that edits are pending.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.3 Status Messages\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `const [saved, setSaved] = useState(true)` with `setSaved(false)`/`setSaved(true)` drive no DOM output; there is no `aria-live=\"polite\"` status node. (The *visual/interaction* half of this defect is the MAJOR Cognitive finding D8a.)\n**Fix:** Render a visually-hidden `aria-live=\"polite\"` region that announces \"You have unsaved changes\" on edit and \"Settings saved\" on success.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 7 \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent (HIGH)\n\n**JTBD checklist:**\n\n| Item (WCAG) | Result | Note |\n|---|---|---|\n| Errors suggest specific corrective action (3.3.3) | **FINDING** | Opaque codes; see D7. |\n| Multi-step form doesn't re-ask info (3.3.7) | N/A | Single step. |\n| Auth no transcription/memory/puzzle (3.3.8) | N/A | No auth. |\n| Nav same relative position across pages (3.2.3) | N/A (verify) | Single component. |\n| Same-function components consistent (3.2.4) | PASS | All toggles use identical checkbox+label pattern. |\n| Help mechanism consistent location (3.2.6) | N/A | No help mechanism exists (its absence tracked under jargon, D9). |\n| Focus does not auto-change context (3.2.1) | PASS | Focus alone triggers nothing. |\n| Changing a control doesn't auto-submit/navigate (3.2.2) | PASS | `onChange` updates local state only \u2014 correctly implemented. |\n| Destructive/consequential actions have undo/confirm/review (3.3.4) | **FINDING** | No confirmation, no unsaved guard; see D8a. |\n| More than one way to reach a page (2.4.5) | N/A | Single component. |\n| Personal-data inputs have `autocomplete` (1.3.5) | N/A | Boolean settings, no personal data. |\n| Timeout warnings \u226520s (2.2.1) | N/A | No timeout. |\n| Avoids unexplained jargon/undefined abbreviations (3.1.3/3.1.4, AAA) | **FINDING** | Dense jargon, no help; see D9. |\n\n**Neurodivergent-specific:**\n\n| Check | Result | Note |\n|---|---|---|\n| Predictable layout, no shifts | PASS | Static layout. |\n| Clear visual hierarchy (headings/spacing/grouping) | **FINDING** | 9px headers invert hierarchy and defeat the visible grouping; see D-hierarchy. |\n| No autoplay media / unprompted modals | PASS | None. |\n| Instructions don't rely on memory of prior steps | PASS | Single step. |\n\n**Red flag check:** CAPTCHA/cognitive-test (none), paste-disabled (none), multi-step re-collection (none) do not fire. \"Destructive action with no confirmation step\" \u2014 I decline to auto-CRITICAL this: \"Save Changes\" is a single, intentional, user-initiated settings write, not a one-click irreversible delete. The genuine harm is (a) silent loss of unsaved edits on navigation and (b) an unreviewed write of consequential production config \u2014 both real, but MAJOR under 3.3.4, not auto-CRITICAL. Calibration reflects user impact, not rule weight.\n\n> **Adversarial note on a planted claim:** the fixture comment asserts \"12 toggles ... no visual grouping into sub-categories \u2014 cognitive overload.\" That is only half true. The toggles *are* grouped into three labeled categories of four (Security / Performance / Logging) \u2014 sound information architecture. Calling this \"no grouping\" would be dead output. The real defect is that the 9px section headers make that grouping visually near-invisible, so it *reads* as an undifferentiated wall of twelve toggles. The fix is header legibility (D2), not adding grouping that already exists.\n\n**Finding:** Error messages are opaque machine codes with no plain-English description or corrective action. \"ERR_CSP_001\" tells the user nothing about what is wrong or how to fix it \u2014 the highest-impact barrier for the cognitive users this perspective protects.\n**WCAG:** 3.3.3 Error Suggestion\n**Perspective:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `SECURITY_TOGGLES` `error: 'ERR_CSP_001'`; rendered verbatim in `.error-inline`; fixture comment \"no human-readable description, no link to documentation\".\n**Fix:** Replace codes with a plain-language message and a remediation step, e.g., \"Content Security Policy can't be enforced until a policy is defined. Add a policy in Security \u2192 CSP, then re-enable.\" Keep the code as secondary/reference text if needed for support.\n\n**Finding:** No unsaved-changes indicator and no confirmation/review of a consequential write. `saved` flips to `false` on any toggle but nothing renders \u2014 the Save button's appearance is unchanged \u2014 so a user can navigate away and silently lose edits; conversely, Save writes production server settings (HSTS, CORS, logging) with no review or confirmation step and no undo.\n**WCAG:** 3.3.4 Error Prevention (Legal, Financial, Data \u2014 server-config modification)\n**Perspective:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** UX Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `handleToggle` calls `setSaved(false)` but the component renders no dependent UI; `.settings-actions` has fixture comment \"no unsaved-changes indicator anywhere\"; `handleSave` commits immediately with no confirm/review. `[Verify save semantics \u2014 confirm whether Save writes live production config immediately, which sets the ceiling on 3.3.4 severity.]`\n**Fix:** Surface a persistent \"You have unsaved changes\" banner and reflect the dirty state on the Save button; add a confirmation/review step (or undo) before applying changes to production; add a navigation guard for pending edits.\n\n**Finding:** Broken visual hierarchy \u2014 section headers are smaller than the labels they group. At 9px, the `<h2>` group titles read as fine print beneath 13px item labels, removing the top-level structure cognitive users rely on to scan and chunk twelve options.\n**WCAG:** 1.3.1 Info and Relationships (visual grouping); shares root cause with Magnification D2 (1.4.4)\n**Perspective:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n**Severity:** MAJOR (counted once, under Magnification D2 \u2014 listed here as the cognitive impact of the same defect, not a separately scored finding)\n**Route to:** Visual Design (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `.settings-column h2 { font-size: 9px }` vs `.toggle-label { font-size: 13px }`.\n**Fix:** Same as D2 \u2014 headers \u226514px and visibly dominant over item labels; consider spacing/dividers between groups.\n\n**Finding:** Required fields have no visible \"Required\" text or legend \u2014 only a `*` with no key explaining it. Sighted cognitive users must infer the asterisk's meaning; there is no form-level instruction (\"* indicates a required setting\").\n**WCAG:** 3.3.2 Labels or Instructions\n**Perspective:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: Front-End Dev)\n**Evidence:** `<span className=\"required-asterisk\" aria-hidden=\"true\">*</span>` is the sole cue; no legend/instruction in `.settings-header` or group headers. (Programmatic-exposure facet is the MAJOR S2 under Screen Reader; contrast facet is C1 under Environmental Contrast \u2014 three distinct fixes, three owners.)\n**Fix:** Add a visible \"Required\" text label or badge on required rows and a form-level legend; pair with the `aria-required` fix (S2).\n\n**Finding:** Dense technical jargon with no glossary, tooltip, or plain-English gloss (\"HSTS preloading\", \"SRI validation\", \"stale-while-revalidate\", \"Immutable audit trail (WAL)\", \"Prometheus metrics endpoint\").\n**WCAG:** 3.1.3 Unusual Words / 3.1.4 Abbreviations (both **AAA**)\n**Perspective:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n**Severity:** ENHANCEMENT (AAA \u2014 never escalated per severity rules)\n**Route to:** Content Author (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `SECURITY_TOGGLES`/`PERFORMANCE_TOGGLES`/`LOGGING_TOGGLES` label strings; fixture comment \"no tooltip or glossary link\".\n**Fix:** Add optional inline definitions/tooltips or a glossary link per setting. Calibration: the audience is server administrators, for whom terms like HSTS/CORS/CSP are domain-standard, so this is a genuine enhancement \u2014 not a shipping blocker. Prioritize the less-universal terms (WAL, stale-while-revalidate).\n\n---\n\n## New-Finding Contract Blocks (CRITICAL + MAJOR)\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: reflow-no-320-single-column\nfingerprint: 3c9a1f77\nsource: perspective-audit Magnification & Reflow checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 1.4.10 Reflow\nsection_508_fpc_context: WCAG 2.1 AA criterion; not in Revised Section 508's WCAG 2.0 A\u2013AA incorporation\nseverity: CRITICAL\nperspective_alarms: magnification_reflow=HIGH\nevidence: CSS `.settings-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px }`; no `@media`/`minmax()`/`auto-fit`; three fixed `.settings-column` siblings\nreproduction_steps: Render at 320px CSS px (or zoom 400% on 1280px viewport); observe horizontal scrollbar (grid min-content exceeds viewport). Visual regression screenshot recommended to confirm.\nexpected_behavior: Content reflows to a single column with no two-axis scrolling\nactual_behavior: Three columns persist; horizontal scroll appears\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: header-9px-illegible-inverts-hierarchy\nfingerprint: 8b21e4a0\nsource: perspective-audit Magnification & Reflow / Cognitive checklists\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 1.4.4 Resize Text (cognitive cross-impact SC 1.3.1)\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 (WCAG 2.0 AA \u2014 1.4.4 and 1.3.1 both incorporated)\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: magnification_reflow=HIGH, cognitive_neurodivergent=HIGH\nevidence: `.settings-column h2 { font-size: 9px; text-transform: uppercase }` vs `.toggle-label { font-size: 13px }`\nreproduction_steps: source review only\nexpected_behavior: Group headers are legible (\u226514px) and visually dominant over item labels\nactual_behavior: 9px uppercase headers are smaller than the 13px labels they group\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: red-text-contrast-413\nfingerprint: c4f0d9e2\nsource: perspective-audit Environmental Contrast checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 1.4.3 Contrast (Minimum)\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 (WCAG 2.0 AA \u2014 1.4.3 incorporated)\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: environmental_contrast=MEDIUM\nevidence: `#e53e3e` on `#fff` = 4.13:1 (< 4.5:1); used in `.error-inline` (11px) and `.required-asterisk` (9px)\nreproduction_steps: Measure `#e53e3e`/`#ffffff` in any contrast tool \u2192 4.13:1\nexpected_behavior: Normal-size text \u2265 4.5:1\nactual_behavior: 4.13:1, below minimum\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: required-state-not-exposed\nfingerprint: a7d2c018\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 (WCAG 2.0 A \u2014 4.1.2 incorporated)\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\nevidence: data `required: true` for hsts/cors/access-log, but JSX emits only `aria-hidden` `*`; no `required`/`aria-required` on `<input>`\nreproduction_steps: Inspect accessibility tree for a required checkbox \u2192 no \"required\" state present\nexpected_behavior: Required toggles expose a programmatic required state to AT\nactual_behavior: No required state in the a11y tree; asterisk is aria-hidden\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: error-not-associated\nfingerprint: f19b6c53\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 3.3.1 Error Identification (with SC 4.1.3)\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 (WCAG 2.0 A \u2014 3.3.1 incorporated; 4.1.3 is WCAG 2.1, not in 508 baseline)\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\nevidence: `<input id={t.id}>` lacks `aria-describedby`/`aria-invalid`; sibling `<span role=\"alert\">{t.error}</span>` unreferenced; error present at mount\nreproduction_steps: Tab to CSP checkbox with a screen reader \u2192 error text is not announced in context\nexpected_behavior: Error is programmatically associated and conveyed when the field receives focus\nactual_behavior: Error is orphaned; alert-on-mount is unreliable\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: error-code-opaque\nfingerprint: 2e88a4bd\nsource: perspective-audit Cognitive & Neurodivergent checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 3.3.3 Error Suggestion\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 (WCAG 2.0 AA \u2014 3.3.3 incorporated)\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: cognitive_neurodivergent=HIGH\nevidence: `error: 'ERR_CSP_001'` rendered verbatim; no plain-language description or corrective action\nreproduction_steps: source review only\nexpected_behavior: Error explains the problem in plain language and suggests a fix\nactual_behavior: Opaque code with no guidance\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: unsaved-changes-no-indicator\nfingerprint: 6d3f0ac9\nsource: perspective-audit Cognitive & Neurodivergent checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 3.3.4 Error Prevention (Legal, Financial, Data)\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 (WCAG 2.0 AA \u2014 3.3.4 incorporated)\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: cognitive_neurodivergent=HIGH, screen_reader_semantic=MEDIUM\nevidence: `setSaved(false)` drives no UI; `.settings-actions` \"no unsaved-changes indicator\"; `handleSave` commits with no confirm/review/undo\nreproduction_steps: Toggle a setting, then navigate away \u2192 edits lost with no warning; click Save \u2192 no confirmation of a production write\nexpected_behavior: Dirty state is visible, consequential save is confirmed/reversible, navigation is guarded\nactual_behavior: Silent dirty state; unconfirmed immediate write; no undo\ntrend: new\n\n---\n\n## Perspective Audit Summary\n\n**Component/artifact reviewed:** Dense Admin Settings Panel With Jargon (`AdminSettings` React component)\n**Perspectives escalated for deep review:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent (HIGH), Magnification & Reflow (HIGH), Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (MEDIUM), Environmental Contrast (MEDIUM)\n**Perspectives at LOW (not reviewed):** Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Auditory Access, Keyboard & Motor Access\n\n### Findings by Severity\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 1 |\n| MAJOR | 6 |\n| MINOR | 3 |\n| ENHANCEMENT | 1 |\n\n> Shared root causes (not double-counted): the 9px header drives both Magnification D2 and the Cognitive hierarchy impact (scored once). \"Required-field indication\" surfaces as three distinct findings with three different owners/fixes \u2014 S2 (aria, MAJOR), C1 (contrast, MAJOR, shared with error text), D5b (visible text, MINOR). \"Save-state feedback\" surfaces as D8a (Cognitive/UX, MAJOR) and S3 (aria-live, MINOR).\n\n### Perspectives That Passed\n\nNone. All four escalated perspectives produced at least one finding. (Individual checklist items that passed are marked PASS in each section \u2014 notably: `<main>` landmark, h1\u2192h2 semantic hierarchy, label/input association, DOM-order match, no auto-context-change on focus/value, 1.4.1 non-color cues present, and adequate contrast on headers/button/body text.)\n\n### Perspectives With Findings \u2014 Grouped by ARRM Role\n\n**Front-End Dev**\n- Validation error not programmatically associated \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 3.3.1 (+4.1.3)\n- Required state not exposed to AT \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.2\n- Save/unsaved status not announced (no aria-live) \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MINOR \u2014 4.1.3\n\n**Visual Design**\n- Layout does not reflow at 320px (two-axis scroll) \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 1.4.10\n- 9px section headers (illegible + inverted hierarchy) \u2014 Magnification & Reflow / Cognitive \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.4.4 (/1.3.1)\n- Red `#e53e3e` error + required text at 4.13:1 \u2014 Environmental Contrast \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 1.4.3\n- Text-spacing override risk in narrow columns \u2014 Magnification & Reflow \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.4.12\n\n**UX Design**\n- No unsaved-changes indicator / no confirmation of consequential save \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 3.3.4\n\n**Content Author**\n- Opaque error codes (\"ERR_CSP_001\") with no remediation \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 3.3.3\n- Required fields lack visible \"Required\" text/legend \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 MINOR \u2014 3.3.2\n- Dense jargon with no glossary/tooltip \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 ENHANCEMENT \u2014 3.1.3/3.1.4 (AAA)\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Human Verification\n\n- **Reflow overflow (D1):** confirm two-axis scrolling at 320px / 400% zoom with a visual-regression screenshot (reasoned from CSS; the *absence* of any reflow rule is provable from source, the exact overflow px is not).\n- **Text-spacing (D3):** apply the WCAG 1.4.12 text-spacing bookmarklet and check for clipping/overlap in the columns.\n- **Save semantics (D8a):** confirm whether \"Save Changes\" writes live production config immediately \u2014 this sets the ceiling on 3.3.4 severity.\n- **Document scope:** `<title>` uniqueness (2.4.2) and `<html lang>` (3.1.1) are not present in the component source \u2014 verify at the page level.\n- **Cross-page items:** navigation consistency (3.2.3) and help-mechanism location (3.2.6) cannot be assessed from a single component.\n\n### Recommended Next Step\n\n**BLOCK** \u2014 one CRITICAL finding (1.4.10 reflow: the panel never collapses to a single column and produces two-axis scrolling at 320px / 400% zoom) makes the panel unusable for magnification users and must be fixed before shipping. Six MAJOR findings additionally require **REVISE** in the same pass: red-text contrast (1.4.3), error-not-associated (3.3.1), required-state-not-exposed (4.1.2), opaque error codes (3.3.3), unsaved-changes/confirmation (3.3.4), and 9px header legibility (1.4.4). Re-run a11y-test (axe-core + keyboard + a 400%/320px reflow screenshot) after fixes.\n",
